{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti 8.413** states the following rule on the duties of a Shudra:\n\n> But he should make a Shudra perform the work of a slave, whether bought or not bought; for he was created by the Self-existent One for the service of a Brahmana.[^1]\n\nThis follows directly from 8.412, which prohibits a Brahmana from forcing twice-born men (Kshatriyas or Vaishyas) into slave labor under penalty of a fine.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/08/translation/#p-e6bdf4).\n[^2]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 8, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/08/translation/#p-67b064).",
